A town known as Ogombo, located in Eti-Osa Local Government Area of Lagos State, has a new traditional ruler, with Prince Abiodun Ogunbo having received his Certificate of Office as the latest Baale of the town. The 46-year old monarch, who emerged from the Ogunbo Royal House, is a prominent indigene of the town who is known to have contributed vastly to the development of the town. He is also the Chief Executive Officer of Asela Group of Companies which is based in Sangotedo. During a brief ceremony held at the Iru/Victoria Island Local Council Development Area Secretariat on Monday, traditional rulers of the local government under the aegis of the Eti-Osa Council of Obas were present to witness the event as led by their chairman, Oba Tijani Adetunji Akinloye, the Ojomu of Ajiranland. Speaking shortly after the ceremony, the newly-installed monarch used the opportunity of the occasion to congratulate new Lagos State governor, Mr. Babajide Sanwoolu and his deputy, Dr Qadri Hamzat. Baale Ogunbo, urged the governor to come to the aid of Ogombo community in the areas of infrastructural development, education and health, among others. Dignitaries from all walks of life including the member representing Eti-Osa Constituency 2 in the state House of Assembly, Mr. Noheem Adams, traditional rulers, religious leaders and members of the Ogombo community graced the epoch occasion.